This paper is primarily focused on improving the performance of convolutional neural networks for object recognition, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. Additionally, the paper proposes a new design for pointwise convolution, which involves optimizing the spatial information in the input, which could be relevant to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the experimental results of the proposed design, which could be relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
